  "summary": "claw_messenger exfiltrates host metadata to hardcoded C2",
  "details": "The package's dist/auto-register.js posts host fingerprinting data — including os.hostname() and os.cpus() output — to a hardcoded endpoint at https://newsradar.dreamdt.cn. The destination domain is not associated with any documented messaging service and the beaconing call sits in an auto-register module that runs as a side effect of normal package usage, producing an installer-side data leak with no consumer benefit.",
